ZCZC OE16
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 122300 UTC
A RIDGE AXIS LOCATED IN THE MID ATLANTIC ON SUNDAY
EVENING WILL MOV EWARDS TO LIE ACROSS THE UK BY THE END
OF MONDAY. A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL DEVELOP TO
THE W OF ICELAND LATER WITH LOW PRESSURE OVER EUROPE AND
THE MEDITERRANEAN SEA. THE RIDGE AXIS WILL DECLINE TO LIE
IN NERN EUROPE BY THE END OF TUESDAY WITH AREAS OF LOW
PRESSURE NEAR ICELAND. A FRONTAL TROUGH WILL THEN EXTEND
SWARDS ACROSS THE UK ON WEDNESDAY. STRG N WINDS ON SUNDAY
EVENING PERHAPS WITH OCCASIONAL GALES IN THE S AT FIRST
WILL MOD THROUGH MONDAY. STRG TO GALE S WINDS WILL
DEVELOP IN ATLANTIC SEA AREAS ON MONDAY WITH SEV GALES IN
ROCKALL BAILEY AND SE ICELAND LATER. GALES OR SEV GALES
ARE EXP IN NERN ATLANTIC SEA AREAS ON TUESDAY AND STRG
TO GALE IN SERNMOST SEA AREAS INCLUDING IRISH SEA. ON
WEDNESDAY WINDS WILL DECREASE IN THE S TO OCNL STRG WITH
GALES IN THE N
